00:09.478 --> 00:13.722
Be sure to subscribe so we can get you these new sermons every week.

00:14.003 --> 00:14.943
Hope you're blessed today.

00:21.269 --> 00:32.480
I am so grateful for Jesus, and I am so grateful for every one of you here today at Elevation Church.

00:32.700 --> 00:34.642
How grateful am I?

00:36.322 --> 00:38.224
and all of our E family.

00:38.244 --> 00:40.207
I've got to say, I'm so excited this morning.

00:40.307 --> 00:46.614
Normally, I'm the one on the other side of the screen because I'll give our literature in a little secret.

00:46.634 --> 00:49.578
You know, I live on the West Coast and say, you're three hours ahead of us.

00:50.118 --> 01:00.210
So before I go and preach on the West Coast, I get a dose of pasta, Steven, Ferdy, before I go and preach every, every Sunday.

01:00.514 --> 01:04.340
I'm so, so grateful for Pastor Stephen and Holly and this church.

01:04.400 --> 01:10.891
Turn to your neighbor and say you are the best looking person I've seen today, wherever you are.

01:10.911 --> 01:12.374
Okay, hang on, just before you sit down.

01:13.355 --> 01:17.703
Turn to your other neighbor, that's your second choice and say you're actually better looking than the other person.

01:17.823 --> 01:19.365
I was lying, I was lying.

01:23.051 --> 01:24.594
You can be seated.

01:25.538 --> 01:31.965
I could not wait to be with my elevation church family today and all our family.

01:32.005 --> 01:39.173
I'm excited because I'm normally that person on the other side of the screen and it is like being home away from home.

01:39.193 --> 01:46.381
You know, when I first started coming here, I am here today with a single most ravishing piece of masculine flesh on planet earth.

01:46.881 --> 01:51.747
And in about two weeks, Nick and I have been married for 30 years.

01:51.907 --> 01:54.770
How is that?

01:55.394 --> 02:00.483
You know, I gotta say, my husband is number 12 of 13 children.

02:02.146 --> 02:04.810
Yes, there was no television in that part of Australia at all.

02:06.713 --> 02:10.620
Nick's mother had 15 full-term pregnancies in 17 years.

02:12.483 --> 02:15.489
Y'all, I just gotta say, every woman in this room just crossed her legs right there.

02:15.509 --> 02:16.370
That was like...

02:17.186 --> 02:18.268
Another level.

02:18.709 --> 02:20.092
I'm glad they didn't stop where they were.

02:20.112 --> 02:23.799
But my mother-in-law, she didn't think you were a chick unless you popped out like 10 kids.

02:23.860 --> 02:24.842
And we've only got two.

02:25.162 --> 02:30.994
So I would take my two daughters, Catherine, and I'd say to my mother-in-law, this is Catherine, and she is my alpha.

02:31.074 --> 02:33.977
And this is Sophia, and she is my Omega.

02:34.037 --> 02:38.420
And this is the beginning and the end of my child, Barry Yeast.

02:38.861 --> 02:41.323
This is where it all stops right here.

02:41.823 --> 02:46.627
And so our daughters, when we started coming to elevation, they were like in single digits.

02:46.688 --> 02:50.711
And now Catherine, she graduated from Pepperdine last May.

02:50.731 --> 02:51.752
I don't know if you know where that is.

02:51.812 --> 02:55.896
Yes, she was suffering for Jesus at Malibu Beach for the last four years.

02:55.916 --> 02:58.258
She was like, here I am, Lord, send me.

02:58.518 --> 03:01.060
And then she went to Argentina and did an internship.

03:01.040 --> 03:03.924
with a church down there, which was fantastic.

03:04.164 --> 03:07.850
And now she's back working with us at A21.

03:08.190 --> 03:11.835
And then our Sophia is studying comparative literature in Paris.

03:12.416 --> 03:13.037
And I know.

03:13.378 --> 03:13.798
I called her.

03:13.818 --> 03:16.262
She's like, Mommy, I can't talk to you right now.

03:16.282 --> 03:21.509
I'm just watching the sunset over Notre Dame eating a chocolate croissant.

03:21.529 --> 03:29.320
To which I replied, sweetheart, if you want to watch that same sunset next semester with your fees paid, you will talk to your mother right now.

03:29.360 --> 03:30.482
That's actually

03:30.850 --> 03:32.212
what you're going to be doing.

03:32.312 --> 03:33.154
There's nothing else.

03:33.594 --> 03:34.996
Don't choke on your croissant.

03:35.097 --> 03:41.887
But anyway, and this is the year that I turn 60.

03:42.007 --> 03:44.992
So I am so excited.

03:45.012 --> 03:49.258
And I have to tell you all that I am celebrating every day.

03:49.358 --> 03:51.201
There is no way I'm waiting to September.

03:51.321 --> 03:58.252
I figure if you live this long and you're not dead, you are celebrating for 365 days.

03:58.352 --> 03:59.474
That's what I'm doing.

04:00.066 --> 04:02.089
So I'm telling you all because I love gifts.

04:02.149 --> 04:02.695
Feel free.

04:02.918 --> 04:03.666
Oh, yeah.

04:04.130 --> 04:10.115
And so I'm also doing 60 things I've never done before, because I want to make sure we finish strong.

04:10.135 --> 04:15.640
We need a generation of young people that can see that the longer you walk with Jesus, the better that it gets.

04:15.760 --> 04:19.203
I'm telling you, I want to run my race and finish my course.

04:19.463 --> 04:26.429
I love being 20, and I love being 30, and I love being 40, and I love being in my 50s, but there is nothing like your sixth decade.

04:26.449 --> 04:27.390
That is the best thing.

04:27.410 --> 04:28.131
So you just wait.

04:28.471 --> 04:30.653
It gets better and better and better.

04:30.713 --> 04:34.116
That is, I mean, how could you fix your eyes on Jesus

04:34.096 --> 04:39.707
for four decades and not grow more in love or grace or peace or goodness or kindness.

04:40.028 --> 04:45.259
You know, some people like, they look like just a whole lot, I don't know, more depressed after 40 years.

04:45.319 --> 04:48.165
I'm like, honey, you could not have fixed your eyes on Jesus.

04:48.566 --> 04:52.754
And then up like that, some people have been in the way for 50 years.

04:52.866 --> 04:53.647
Get out of the way.

04:53.668 --> 04:58.797
Anyway, so I told my daughters, I'm going to be super granny for Jesus.

04:59.098 --> 05:00.180
I'm going to be like Caleb.

05:00.480 --> 05:04.268
He said, I'm 85 and I'm as strong now as I was then.

05:04.328 --> 05:05.690
Now, give me this mountain.

05:05.710 --> 05:06.812
That's my inheritance.

05:07.233 --> 05:08.435
I'm going in to take it.

05:08.475 --> 05:10.720
So it just gets better.

05:10.800 --> 05:12.223
You young ones, you don't even know.

05:12.263 --> 05:14.046
You don't even know yet.

05:14.066 --> 05:15.248
Why don't I tell you all that for?

05:15.268 --> 05:16.210
Because I'm doing

05:16.642 --> 05:18.444
60 things I've never done.

05:18.765 --> 05:19.706
And that could be anything.

05:19.766 --> 05:22.350
It could be like, you know, really big things, really little things.

05:22.470 --> 05:28.719
And, you know, so I live in California and we, that is the home of in and out.

05:28.839 --> 05:29.279
I don't know.

05:29.319 --> 05:30.060
Do you have in and out?

05:30.241 --> 05:30.761
Yes.

05:31.302 --> 05:31.743
Okay.

05:31.803 --> 05:35.828
And they're going to be serving that at the marriage supper of the lamb in case anybody was not sure.

05:36.549 --> 05:43.118
And so I thought after like three decades of going to Texas, I thought, okay, this is my 60th year.

05:43.139 --> 05:44.240
I'm going to do things I've never done.

05:44.701 --> 05:45.682
So I tried.

05:45.890 --> 05:46.554
What a burger.

05:49.068 --> 05:50.053
That was a once and done.

05:50.114 --> 05:52.306
Now moving on to the...

05:52.514 --> 05:54.756
And then I'd never seen the Northern Lights.

05:54.816 --> 05:59.280
So Nick took me to Alaska to see the Northern Lights and stained an igloo.

05:59.420 --> 06:02.423
And I thought, next time we want to go to an igloo, you can go by yourself.

06:02.483 --> 06:03.744
OK, so it was awesome.

06:04.164 --> 06:05.846
But we also did that.

06:05.926 --> 06:09.068
And I've got to tell you to give some of you some excitement to keep going.

06:09.108 --> 06:12.231
I've been almost four decades in full-time vocational ministry.

06:12.251 --> 06:14.913
And the Lords allowed us to do lots of things.

06:14.994 --> 06:22.500
But I did get, I just want to tell you, because I did get a first, which for me, you know, I've written 12 books and done a lot of ministry in nearly four decades.

06:22.480 --> 06:28.251
but last week the faith to flourish came out and it was the first time I got a New York Times bestseller.

06:28.311 --> 06:30.576
How is that the first time?

06:30.596 --> 06:34.924
So I'm telling you that because life does not stop when you're 60.

06:34.985 --> 06:39.794
There's a whole lot of firsts ahead of you and you know I just truly believe.

06:39.970 --> 06:44.016
that it is the will of God that the body of Christ begins to flourish again.

06:44.036 --> 06:54.111
And, you know, we dive deep into the life of the olive tree because I was reading some 52 verse 8 and David in the midst of his darkest hour.

06:54.131 --> 06:55.433
There was so much adversity.

06:55.733 --> 06:58.578
He was, Saul was chasing him to kill him.

06:58.918 --> 07:00.420
Doeg was after him.

07:00.440 --> 07:06.249
There was so much betrayal and lies and slander and gossip and darkness.

07:06.530 --> 07:08.332
And he was in fear of his physical life.

07:08.412 --> 07:09.554
And yet in the midst of it,

07:09.954 --> 07:15.218
He said, but I am like a green olive tree, flourishing.

07:15.394 --> 07:16.555
in the house of God.

07:16.835 --> 07:22.820
And he was speaking of his deliverance and his state, regardless of his external circumstances.

07:23.141 --> 07:45.380
And I was standing, we have an A21 office in Athens in Greece, and I was taking a team there, we went up to the top of the Acropolis to see the Parthenon, and it's barren, and it's arid, and it's dry, and everything, it was in the middle of the, there had been great fires in Athens, there was a great heat wave, and there was no other trees that were alive, there was nothing

07:45.360 --> 07:51.132
There was no vegetation and there was this one and if you go up to the path and you'll see it, this sacred olive tree.

07:51.894 --> 08:03.698
And here in the midst of barrenness, here in the midst of a place where nothing else is growing, there is this green olive tree whose root system goes deep that is

08:03.746 --> 08:13.094
flourishing and thriving and producing fruit and producing an ecosystem and keeping other things alive and giving them shelter and producing oil.

08:13.534 --> 08:20.741
And I sat there and I went to eight countries, went to visit olive farms on eight different countries, talked to the owners of olive farms to see.

08:21.441 --> 08:22.662
I have nerded out so much.

08:22.722 --> 08:27.507
I know more about olive trees, olive oil, olive branches and olives than you would ever want, but I'm Greek.

08:27.567 --> 08:30.709
And so if you've seen my big fat Greek wedding, that is my big fat Greek life.

08:30.769 --> 08:32.231
You had milk in your baby bottle.

08:32.331 --> 08:33.732
I had olive oil.

08:33.712 --> 08:40.699
So the issue is out of that, that an olive tree grows when nothing else grows and continues to breed life.

08:40.740 --> 08:45.445
And in scripture, there are over 200 references to olive trees, olive oil, olive branches.

08:45.865 --> 09:03.684
And I think in this hour where our world is so chaotic, it's so full of division, it's so full of fear, it's so full of darkness and economic instability and political instability and moral instability and sociological instability, we, the Church of Jesus Christ, need to be like a green olive tree flourishing and producing

09:03.664 --> 09:10.196
life and it will be one of the greatest witnesses to our generation if we would dare do that.

09:10.296 --> 09:16.667
So I was excited about writing that message and I'm believing to equip us to do it.

09:16.988 --> 09:25.202
And I also want to say thank you to every one of you because Elevation Church is such a key partner church right from day one of

09:25.346 --> 09:32.532
821 and I just want to testify because so many of you, especially during Love Week, you are involved in packing packages.

09:33.493 --> 09:55.332
We've got an office here in Charlotte and so much of what you pack goes to survivors like we go out with law enforcement when there are raids done and when there are operations done and sometimes we're the first port of contact with victims and survivors and because of your giving and because of your generosity

09:55.312 --> 10:02.120
We are able to give packs that bring dignity to the women and the children right in those moments of crisis.

10:02.640 --> 10:06.985
But I do want to tell you, because there's a case that we've been working on for nine years.

10:07.045 --> 10:08.147
This is how long it takes.

10:08.507 --> 10:09.308
Nine years.

10:09.809 --> 10:19.239
And last week, the guy from Charlotte that had trafficked multiple women across 51 cities, 15 states, we put him away for 35 years.

10:19.480 --> 10:20.160
How is that?

10:20.721 --> 10:21.522
Right here.

10:21.826 --> 10:23.449
in Charlotte, North Carolina.

10:23.489 --> 10:25.452
So that is what your giving is doing.

10:26.034 --> 10:28.698
And so I am so, so grateful.

10:28.758 --> 10:32.064
I could keep you here and tell your story after story.

10:32.084 --> 10:35.991
But I told you we've been married 30 years in March.

10:36.472 --> 10:37.554
And Nick and I

10:37.602 --> 10:44.008
I mean, he's from an English Irish background, I'm from a Greek background, so I'm demonstrative in every way.

10:44.508 --> 10:57.019
My inside voice is my outside voice, is my every voice, and Nick is like Christine, I am excited in worship, my big toe is moving in my shoe, you know, so, and I'm like in orbit, like, who am I?

10:57.039 --> 10:59.341
I'm like, I nearly was up there through the sky today.

11:00.021 --> 11:07.588
And so, but I'm also meticulous, he would say, borderline OCD anyway, I'm very meticulous, and we have a mantra in our

11:07.568 --> 11:12.556
house since my girls were like, came in utero.

11:12.576 --> 11:23.513
We had a mantra and we would say, and I would say, girls, there is a place for everything and everything has a place.

11:23.974 --> 11:25.256
See, you're just like me.

11:25.837 --> 11:33.970
But Nick, Nick is of the opinion that there are many potential places for everyone thing.

11:34.050 --> 11:48.131
Let me just say that over 30 years there have been some, not many, but frequent, times of intense fellowship over which one of the many places, next keys, may have been in.

11:48.171 --> 11:52.197
And if we just put them in the one place, we would have avoided.

11:52.217 --> 11:55.602
There would have been much more fruit of the spirit in our household.

11:55.778 --> 12:01.607
