12:13.965 --> 12:19.273
So we're not going, I'm watching nudging, happening and heads moving.

12:19.293 --> 12:25.042
But I do have to say that after almost four decades of serving Jesus, it is nice.

12:25.474 --> 12:27.296
when God agrees with you.

12:27.356 --> 12:38.909
And so in my quiet time when I came across 1 Corinthians chapter 12, I needed to take it to Nick to show him that God and I were in the same place.

12:39.249 --> 12:43.974
We were on the same page when it comes to the fact that there is a place for everything.

12:44.235 --> 12:50.141
And I had to dig into the 1984 NIV version.

12:50.221 --> 12:54.706
Today we have come to real church here at Elevation to pull out

12:54.818 --> 12:58.183
First Corinthians chapter 12 verses 12 to 27, I'm gonna read this to you.

12:58.203 --> 12:58.944
This is the word of the Lord.

12:59.344 --> 13:02.408
The body is a unit, though it is made up of many parts.

13:02.889 --> 13:08.777
And though all its parts are many, they form one body, so it is with Christ.

13:10.600 --> 13:17.429
For we were all baptized by one spirit into one body, whether Jews or Greeks, slave or free.

13:17.930 --> 13:21.335
And we were all given the one spirit to drink.

13:22.456 --> 13:23.858
Now, the body's not made

13:24.258 --> 13:26.882
up of one part, but of many.

13:26.902 --> 13:36.357
If the foot should say, because I'm not a hand, I do not belong to the body, it would not for that reason cease to be part of the body.

13:37.159 --> 13:45.192
And if the ears should say, because I'm not an eye, I do not belong to the body, it would not for that reason cease to be part of the body.

13:46.273 --> 13:49.579
If the whole body were an eye, where would the sense of hearing be?

13:50.059 --> 13:51.762
If the whole body were an ear,

13:51.906 --> 13:54.129
Where would the sense of smell be?

13:54.189 --> 14:04.103
But in fact, God has arranged the parts of the body, every one of them, just as He wanted them to be.

14:05.365 --> 14:07.448
If they were all one part, where would the body be?

14:07.488 --> 14:11.433
As it is, there are many parts but one body.

14:12.515 --> 14:14.337
The eye cannot stay to the hand, I don't need you.

14:14.377 --> 14:17.842
And the head cannot stay to the feet, I don't need you.

14:18.466 --> 14:35.686
On the contrary, those parts of the body that seem to be weaker are indispensable, and the parts we think are less honourable, we treat with special honour, and the parts that are unpresentable are treated with special modesty, while our presentable parts need no special treatment.

14:36.207 --> 14:45.618
But God has combined the members of the body and has given greater honour to the parts that lacked it, so that there should be no division in the body,

14:45.890 --> 14:50.058
but that its parts should have equal concern for each other.

14:50.960 --> 14:53.645
If one part suffers, every part suffers with it.

14:54.066 --> 14:57.853
If one part is on it, every part rejoices with it.

14:59.036 --> 15:04.947
Now you are the body of Christ and each one of you is a part of it.

15:05.729 --> 15:06.450
I love this

15:06.562 --> 15:19.670
portion of Scripture, Paul was writing to the church in Corinth who was incredibly divided, especially in the way that they were ranking the value of spiritual gifts.

15:19.690 --> 15:25.362
And so the fact is that they were thinking that the more visible gifts

15:25.634 --> 15:34.891
And that they were the more important gifts, the more spectacular, especially when it came to the charismatic gifts, or they have to be the more important gifts.

15:34.971 --> 15:38.618
So what that was causing was division and hierarchy.

15:38.939 --> 15:45.170
And yet God had set every part of the body in place just as he saw

15:45.218 --> 15:45.879
fit.

15:45.899 --> 15:48.183
He has a place for every single part.

15:48.203 --> 15:49.445
There's no hierarchy.

15:49.705 --> 15:59.341
It doesn't rank as important because there's only one body indwelled by the Holy Spirit of God and there's only one head on this body and his name is King Jesus.

15:59.401 --> 16:11.000
He is the head of his body and every other part, every other part has a very important place to play in the body of Christ.

16:11.060 --> 16:12.242
Now what happens

16:12.706 --> 16:22.223
is in our culture that so elevates visibility and confuses prominence and visibility with significance.

16:22.243 --> 16:28.594
We end up having a problem in the church because culture says if you have more followers, you're more important.

16:28.738 --> 16:37.325
If you're a greater celebrity and more people know your name, somehow you are more important or you have greater influence, so you are more important.

16:37.345 --> 16:39.447
That's not how the body works.

16:39.467 --> 16:58.724
Just because someone you today, you see me here on this platform in the eyes of God and in the church of God and in the body of Christ, I am no more important than any other part of the body because God sets every member in place in his body.

16:58.704 --> 16:59.785
his body.

17:00.967 --> 17:09.418
But we can bring into our commitment to the Lord the same thinking that the world has, i.e.

17:09.458 --> 17:12.782
we confuse visibility with significance.

17:14.445 --> 17:19.892
We confuse reach and being known with significance to God.

17:20.432 --> 17:24.658
But here in this passage Paul says there's not one part that's dispensable.

17:24.930 --> 17:33.159
There's not one single part of the body of Christ that is not an important part and doesn't have a place in the body.

17:33.500 --> 17:39.927
Just because you can't see them doesn't mean that they are in any way of any less value.

17:40.388 --> 17:52.882
Now the fact is, you see me here, you see the worship team here, Pastor Jonathan today, but before we even woke up this morning, there was people that were getting up and praying

17:53.186 --> 17:57.230
for all of our locations, for our eFAM, for all of our services.

17:57.330 --> 18:01.373
People that nobody even has ever seen, you don't know their names.

18:01.713 --> 18:08.219
There are people working in the parking lot that are getting ready, that are directing traffic.

18:08.239 --> 18:17.007
There are people right now, without children, teaching them about the importance of the Word of God, people that are teaching our teenagers.

18:17.347 --> 18:23.172
There are people that are working in the sound and the light and people that

18:23.152 --> 18:37.522
working the scriptures going up on screen or making sure that there is connection for even you can't see any of them but let me just say if this microphone went off we would all suffer if one part suffers

18:37.858 --> 18:38.759
everyone suffers.

18:39.200 --> 18:50.194
If there was no one to turn the lights on, if there was no one that was praying, if there was no one that was serving our children or our kids or in the parking lot, then we would all suffer.

18:50.474 --> 18:59.466
But what happens is we've learned to think that the only thing that matters in the body is the prominent positions and somehow that prominence is more significant to God.

18:59.726 --> 19:05.714
But God says it's my body and I set every member in place in my body.

19:08.130 --> 19:10.173
God sets the members in place.

19:11.535 --> 19:26.695
Now, you know, it's so interesting and I don't think we understand really the value of what it means that if one part suffers, every part suffers, a few years ago, you know, really when we moved to America, I went skiing foremost the first time in my life.

19:26.735 --> 19:32.282
What had happened is I'm from a Greek background and church, you have to understand that Greeks are fatalist.

19:32.422 --> 19:35.346
By that, I mean, it does not matter how bad things are.

19:35.554 --> 19:37.876
they can always get worse with a Greek family.

19:38.397 --> 19:46.906
And so I grew up in a Greek home where my mother would always say, Christina, we speak Greek is my first language and we have Windex in every room of the house.

19:46.966 --> 19:54.334
And so she goes, Christina, you can't go skiing because if you go skiing, you will die.

19:55.575 --> 19:58.077
There was no possibility you could go skiing and ski.

19:58.258 --> 19:59.719
It was like ski equals death.

20:00.160 --> 20:02.482
So when we finally moved to America,

20:02.658 --> 20:06.286
I felt like I was a 14-hour plane ride away from my Greek mother.

20:06.707 --> 20:08.692
I know I was 45, but I was still scared of her.

20:08.712 --> 20:11.678
So it was like, OK, I can now do what I want, finally.

20:12.019 --> 20:15.186
And so these five families from Louisiana.

20:15.458 --> 20:18.663
invited us to go skiing in Colorado.

20:18.703 --> 20:23.490
Now, this was during the Winter Olympics, and I know I'm from Australia, so I could surf.

20:23.590 --> 20:25.473
I thought surfing and skiing were the same thing.

20:25.894 --> 20:27.015
